article.headline: Four Tulane players in double figures
article.linkText: Tulane rallies in second half to upset Boston College
article.story:
NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Delacey Joseph had 16 points to lead four
Tulane players in double figures, and the Green Wave rallied in the
second half to upset Boston College (No. 19 ESPN/USA Today, No. 20 AP) 69-50 Sunday.

	   Joseph was 7-of-14 from the field and 2-of-4 from the 3-point
range. She also had five assists for Tulane (8-2). Teana McKiver
added 15 points, Gwen Slaughter 14 and Britt Themann 13.

	   Brianne Stepherson led Boston College (7-3) with 17 points, six
rebounds and five assists. She shot 7-of-14 from the field and
3-of-4 from the free-throw line.

	   On 56-percent shooting, Tulane outscored Boston College 45-21 in
the second half after trailing 29-24 at the break. The Eagles made
only nine of 23 shots in the final 20 minutes.

	   Tulane hit 18-of-32 shots -- including five of seven 3-pointers --
in the second half.

	   Tulane turned over the ball 13 times and Boston College 11.
Boston College also outrebounded Tulane 38-33, but the Green Wave
had 25 assists to 11 for the Eagles.
